    "Chen et al.",
    "85 investigated the dependence between the manufacturing condition and film performance through a combination of supervised learning and unsupervised learning.",
    "Polymer electrolyte is another main category of solid-state electrolyte.",
    "Currently, the primary challenge in developing polymer electrolytes lies in achieving both high ionic conductivity and sufficient modulus simultaneously 86.",
    "The strategies to develop nonflammable polymer solid-state electrolyte composite systems with synergistically enhanced ionic conductivity and modulus involve utilizing polymers with controlled morphological and architecture 87, phase separation 88, anisotropic alignment 89, charged groups 59, 90 and embedded non-flammable ionic liquids 7, [91] [92] [93]."
